The paper deals with a distributed algorithmic problem of reconfiguring maximal independent sets in a graph. This problem involves communication and coordination among nodes, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The problem also involves graph theory concepts such as independent sets and dominating sets, which are part of the subfield of algorithms and data structures for graphs (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of finding certain types of dominating sets, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The problem of reconfiguring independent sets can also be seen as a problem in social networks or network science (cs.SI), as it involves changing the membership of nodes in a network. Finally, the paper discusses the impossibility of obtaining certain types of independent sets, which is related to the theory of network information (cs.NI).
